  "subtitle": "Italian shortcrust tart with a sweetened ricotta filling",
  "excerpt": "A classic Italian Easter tart with a crumbly pasta frolla pastry shell filled with sweetened ricotta, eggs, mixed peel, and cinnamon. The filling is richer and denser than a baked cheesecake and has a matte, slightly grainy texture from the ricotta. Finished with a lattice of pastry strips across the top. Eaten at room temperature, the tart improves in texture overnight once the ricotta sets properly.",
