          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Method"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Make the pastry"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Pulse or rub the flour, butter, sugar, and salt together until crumbly. Add the egg yolks and lemon zest and juice and bring together into a dough. Divide into two-thirds and one-third. Flatten each into a disc, wrap, and refrigerate for 1 hour."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Line the tin and make the filling"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Heat the oven to 180°C conventional (160°C fan). Roll the larger disc of pastry on a floured surface and line a 23 cm deep tart tin, pressing into the sides. Trim the excess. Beat together the drained ricotta, sugar, eggs, vanilla, mixed peel, cinnamon, and lemon juice until smooth. Pour into the pastry shell."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Lattice and bake"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Roll the remaining third of pastry into strips about 1.5 cm wide. Lay strips across the top of the filling in a lattice pattern, pressing the ends against the pastry rim to seal. Bake for 40 to 45 minutes until the pastry is golden and the filling is set with only a slight wobble at the centre. Cool completely in the tin on a rack before unmoulding."
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
